@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Abstracon' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The idea is to place tiles so that all spaces on a board are
filled up with tiles that have various 'abstract' patterns and
those tiles must make a 'path' from the top starting position to
the exit position located at the lower position of a game board.

  Gameplay is quite simple: click on any space that is either empty
or already occupied by a tile. If a tile is at the clicked position,
it will be exchanged with the one that is located under the 'Next'
word, shown at the right of the game board. If there are no Next
tile, the clicked tile will go there.

  Each tile has two 'notches' indicating the points where it can
connect with other tiles, or with the entry or exit. The coloured
pattern of the tile also start and end at these points of
connection.

  As any tile has its place on a game board, the thing is to know
exactly where to put a particular tile... Sometimes there may be
more than one solution for a gameboard...

  The number of moves is added for each game board, and the total
amount of moves is accumulated as you complete each game board...
so the least amount of moves you make for each board, the better
it is...

  Note that as the arrangement of colours for the abstract
patterns on the tiles and their position are strictly random, so
there is no need to put tiles of same colour consecutively...

  That is all there is to it... just play the game!...

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's close button or
press the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

